President Donald J. Trump met with senior defense and military leaders to discuss progress in protecting the homeland, advancing American prosperity, pursuing peace through strength, and promoting positive American influence abroad. The President praised their efforts in defeating ISIS, pursuing a more aggressive campaign in Afghanistan, countering North Korea and Iran, and assisting with hurricane relief efforts. President Trump also expressed his gratitude for the servicemen and women serving in defense of the nation. Following the meeting, the President and First Lady hosted a dinner with the leaders and their spouses to discuss the challenges faced by military families.